<figureCitation box="[452,536,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1566,1588]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,700,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[184,1403,700,1545]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Measured genitalia structures based on the example of C. (P.) agnitaria a) — male, b) — female. ae. l: aedeagus length; an. l: antrum length; an. w: antrum width; slf. l: length of longitudinal spined folding; tl: total length; vm. l: length of ventral valva margin. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040089/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
). Total length: 2.31– 
<quantity box="[776,882,476,500]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.30 mm</quantity>
; length of ventral valva margin: 
<quantity box="[1263,1432,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.725" metricValueMax="1.84" metricValueMin="1.61" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="1.725" valueMax="1.84" valueMin="1.61">1.61–1.84 mm</quantity>
; uncus and gnathos both blunt and strongly sclerotized, gnathos slender, hook-like; juxta almost symmetrical; sclerotized dilation close to base of costa with serrate keel, not swollen; aedeagus length: 
<quantity box="[1156,1322,548,572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.14" metricValueMax="2.24" metricValueMin="2.04" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="2.14" valueMax="2.24" valueMin="2.04">2.04–2.24 mm</quantity>
; aedeagus with cornutus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
Female genitalia (Pl. 3, 
<figureCitation box="[480,562,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1566,1588]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,700,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[184,1403,700,1545]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Measured genitalia structures based on the example of C. (P.) agnitaria a) — male, b) — female. ae. l: aedeagus length; an. l: antrum length; an. w: antrum width; slf. l: length of longitudinal spined folding; tl: total length; vm. l: length of ventral valva margin. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040089/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
). Total length: 
<quantity box="[742,897,620,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.055" metricValueMax="5.71" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="5.055" valueMax="5.71" valueMin="4.4">4.4–5.71 mm</quantity>
; antrum length: 
<quantity box="[1090,1260,620,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.36" metricValueMax="1.37" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="1.36" valueMax="1.37" valueMin="1.35">1.35–1.37 mm</quantity>
; antrum width: 
<quantity box="[151,317,656,680]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="8.7" metricValueMin="7.7" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="0.82" valueMax="0.87" valueMin="0.77">0.77–0.87 mm</quantity>
; length of spined longitudinal folding: 
<quantity box="[753,918,656,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03" metricValueMax="1.12" metricValueMin="0.94" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="1.03" valueMax="1.12" valueMin="0.94">0.94–1.12 mm</quantity>
; antrum relatively short and stout, postvaginal plate almost not extending the antrum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,727,752]" pageId="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[583,754,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[583,754,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,876,728,751]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1877" box="[1151,1352,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creperaria" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[1151,1352,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) creperaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Gnophos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochrofasciata" subGenus="Pterygnophos">C. (P.) ochrofasciata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Both 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[426,669,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[426,669,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="10">Charissa (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[677,788,765,788]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1877" box="[843,1041,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creperaria" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[843,1041,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) creperaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a sclerotized dilation close to the base of the costa but in 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[459,627,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[459,627,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,746,800,823]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
this structure is not swollen and has a serrate keel, while it is bloated and covered with minute spines in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1877" box="[630,827,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creperaria" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[630,827,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) creperaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[842,911,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[172,1401,1534,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[172,1409,1534,1889]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Detail of valva with arrows pointing at diagnostic characters. A — C. (P.) beljaevi spec. nov.; B — C. (P.) creperaria." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040093/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[932,1238,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochrofasciata" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[932,1238,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="10">Charissa (P.) ochrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[250,365,872,895]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the shape of the short valva process but besides the fact that the above mentioned valva sclerotization is absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[439,670,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochrofasciata" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[439,670,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) ochrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species can be recognized by its costal thorns, situated proximal to the setae covered apex. Regarding the female genitalia, identification of 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[991,1158,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[991,1158,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1165,1277,944,967]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is possible on the basis of the antrum, which is shorter than in the other species (antrum length: 
<quantity box="[1068,1231,980,1005]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.36" metricValueMax="1.37" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="1.36" valueMax="1.37" valueMin="1.35">1.35–1.37 mm</quantity>
at maximum) and the postvaginal plate is not strongly extending the antrum as it is in the female genitalia of the other species of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[262,418,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="10">Pterygnophos</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1087,1112]" pageId="10">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[366,440,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1152,1174]" captionTargetBox="[168,1416,229,1131]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[168,1419,229,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Charissa (Pterygnophos) species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040095/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[524,622,1087,1112]" pageId="10">holotype</typeStatus>
and two 
<typeStatus box="[743,850,1088,1112]" pageId="10">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[900,1079,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[900,1079,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1092,1210,1088,1111]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
originate from the Monastery of Amarbayasgalant located in 
<collectingRegion box="[654,855,1124,1149]" country="Mongolia" name="Selenge" pageId="10">Selenge Province</collectingRegion>
(
<quantity box="[875,968,1124,1149]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="10" unit="m" value="1060.0">1060 m</quantity>
) and three further 
<typeStatus box="[1198,1305,1125,1149]" pageId="10">paratypes</typeStatus>
have been captured around 
<collectingRegion box="[339,464,1159,1184]" country="Mongolia" name="Ulaanbaatar" pageId="10">Ulan Bator</collectingRegion>
, both in 
<collectingCountry box="[561,674,1159,1184]" name="Mongolia" pageId="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1051,1196,1221]" pageId="10" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" box="[199,1051,1196,1221]" pageId="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1196,1221]" pageId="10">Biology.</emphasis>
All known specimens have been collected in the beginning of July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1231,1256]" pageId="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
Males and females of the new species were assigned to each other by 
<collectionCode box="[1095,1156,1232,1256]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="10">DNA</collectionCode>
barcoding analyzed with 
<collectionCode box="[151,227,1268,1292]" pageId="10">BOLD</collectionCode>
(http://www.boldsystems.org).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
Based on available molecular data the nearest species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher, 2017" authorityName="Erlacher &amp; Palma &amp; Erlacher" authorityYear="2017" box="[839,1008,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beljaevi" status="spec. nov." subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[839,1008,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) beljaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1015,1127,1305,1328]" pageId="10" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1877" box="[1160,1359,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Charissa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="creperaria" subGenus="Pterygnophos">
<emphasis box="[1160,1359,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="10">C. (P.) creperaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a 
<collectionCode box="[151,199,1340,1364]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="10">COI</collectionCode>
distance of 2.66% (see also 
<tableCitation box="[523,593,1340,1365]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,239,764,787]" captionText="TABLE 1. Genetic distances (minimum pairwise distances, Kimura 2 parameter) to the nearest neighbor of four species of Charissa, subgenus Pterygnophos resulting from a barcode gap analysis of full-length barcode fragments using the analytical tools of BOLD (COI 5 ’, 658 bp)." pageId="10">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[649,717,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1152,1174]" captionTargetBox="[168,1416,229,1131]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[168,1419,229,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Charissa (Pterygnophos) species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1040095/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The morphology of male and female genitalia also indicates a close relationship between these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1473]" pageId="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1412,1437]" pageId="10">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to our colleague and friend Eugeniy A. Beljaev, Vladivostok, 
<collectingCountry box="[1355,1432,1412,1437]" name="Russia" pageId="10">Russia</collectingCountry>
, a leading authority in Geometrid moths of the Far East, in recognition of his consistent great willingness to help.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
